CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 25, 1955, pg. 12, reads: "Pioneers Fete Mothers... and Miss Dolly Johnson at the group's last meeting for the summer season. Held last Saturday afternoon at McNeil's, those mothers of the Pioneers honored included the abover group. Seated, left to right: Mmes. William Eckstein, Estella Leftridge, Miss Dolly Johnson and Mrs. Thorny Ball. Standing in same order: Mmes. Lula Proctor Lewis, Bertha Brown, Cora Cheatham, Hallie Woodson and William Stanton. - 'Teenie' Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of members of Mothers of the Pioneers group, including seated from left: Mrs. William Eckstein, Estella Leftridge, Dolly Johnson, Mrs. Thorny Ball; standing: Lula Proctor Lewis, Bertha Brown, Cora Cheatham, Hallie Woodson and Mrs. William Stanton, posed behind square table, in McNeil's interior, another version
